My Cat4k (console port) in the lab is hooked up to a Cisco C2511 Access server
(term server), line 5.

Term server's IP: 172.22.94.96
Port for my Cat4k: 2006

To connect: telnet 172.22.94.96 2006
Cat4k config reg is set to 0 (boot to Rommon)
To load Cat4k image from frash, type boot.
Or boot <file> to boot from tftp file in /tftpboot/ytse/.

Only one connection to the console port is supported.  To clear the line,
telnet into the access server "telent 172.22.94.96", pw cisco,
"enable" pw cisco123, then "clear line 6".


Term server: pb-ts
pw: lab
en pw: lab


To skip diags:
Add to Cat4k ROMMON:
  SkipDiagsAlways=1


To change boot flash
  copy tftp bootflash

boot bootflash:filename


To disable console timemout:
  config t
  line console 0
  exec-timeout 0 0

--------------------------------------------------------------

The boot flash on standby SUP is slavebootflash:

Need to squeeze <filesystem> to clean up the flash!

To check if a C file in SUP code compiles:
  cd /vob/ios.comp/rfgw/sup/objects/ios.hc.ppc.403
  make <file>.o

--------------------------------------------------------------

To add new subsystem:

Need to modify /vob/ios.comp/rfgw/sup/src/src.mk
Also need to include it in /vob/ios/sys/obj-ppc-rfgw/makesubsys.rfgw

I also probably need to "make cleanderived" and "make derived"
under /vob/ios.comp/rfgw.
